---
import LayoutV2 from "@layouts/LayoutV2.astro";
import Footer from "@components/v2/Footer.astro";

const updated = "15 June 2026";
const contact = "swimwitheddy@gmail.com";
---

<LayoutV2 title="Privacy Policy — Eddy" description="How Eddy collects, uses and protects your information.">
  <header class="legal-top">
    <div class="wrap">
      <a href="/" class="brand" aria-label="Eddy home">
        <span class="mark"><img src="/logo.png" alt="" /></span>
        <span class="name">Eddy</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/" class="back">← Back to home</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="legal">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow"><span class="pip"></span> Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p>
        This policy explains what personal information we collect when you join the Eddy
        waitlist or visit this website, how we use it, and the rights you have over it.
        We've tried to keep it short and in plain English.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        The data controller responsible for your information is <strong>Toby Redshaw</strong>,
        trading as “Eddy”, based in London, United Kingdom. If you have any questions about this
        policy or your data, you can reach us at <a href={`mailto:${contact}`}>{contact}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>2. What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Your email address</strong> — when you submit it through one of the waitlist forms on this site.</li>
        <li><strong>Limited, privacy-friendly analytics</strong> — anonymous, aggregated information about how the site is used (for example, which pages are viewed), which does not identify you.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not ask for, or collect, any other personal details at this stage.</p>

      <h2>3. Why we use it, and our lawful basis</h2>
      <p>
        We use your email address solely to add you to our waitlist and to send you occasional
        updates about Eddy — most importantly, to let you know when it's ready for you. Our lawful
        basis for this is your <strong>consent</strong>, which you give by submitting your email.
        You can withdraw that consent at any time (see section 8).
      </p>

      <h2>4. The service we use to manage emails</h2>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Mailchimp</strong> (a product of Intuit Inc.) to store waitlist emails and
        send messages. Mailchimp acts as our data processor and only handles your information on our
        instructions. You can read Mailchimp's own privacy practices on their website.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Our analytics tool, <strong>Umami</strong>, is cookieless and does not collect personal data
        or track you across other websites. This site does not set advertising or tracking cookies,
        so no cookie consent banner is required.
      </p>

      <h2>6. International transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Because Mailchimp is a US-based provider, your email address may be processed outside the UK.
        Where this happens, it is protected by appropriate safeguards (such as the UK extension to the
        EU–US Data Privacy Framework and/or Standard Contractual Clauses).
      </p>

      <h2>7. How long we keep it</h2>
      <p>
        We keep your email only for as long as we run the waitlist, or until you ask us to remove it
        or unsubscribe — whichever comes first. After that, it is deleted.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK data protection law you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>access the personal data we hold about you;</li>
        <li>have inaccurate data corrected;</li>
        <li>have your data erased;</li>
        <li>restrict or object to how we use it;</li>
        <li>receive a copy of your data (data portability); and</li>
        <li>withdraw your consent at any time.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these, just email us at <a href={`mailto:${contact}`}>{contact}</a>.</p>

      <h2>9. Unsubscribing</h2>
      <p>
        Every email we send includes an unsubscribe link. Clicking it removes you from the waitlist
        immediately. You can also email us and we'll remove you.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Complaints</h2>
      <p>
        If you're unhappy with how we've handled your information, you can contact us first, or make a
        complaint to the UK's data protection regulator, the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO),
        at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. If we make significant changes, we'll update the
        date at the top of this page.
      </p>

      <p class="back-cta"><a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</LayoutV2>

<style>
  .legal-top {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg);
  }
  .legal-top .wrap {
    max-width: var(--maxw);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px 34px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .legal-top .brand { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
  .legal-top .mark {
    width: 38px; height: 38px; border-radius: 12px;
    display: grid; place-items: center; flex: none; background: var(--teal);
  }
  .legal-top .mark img { width: 23px; height: 23px; }
  .legal-top .name {
    font-family: var(--sans); font-weight: 300; font-size: 24px;
    line-height: 1; color: var(--ink);
  }
  .legal-top .back { font-size: 14.5px; font-weight: 500; color: var(--fg-2); }
  .legal-top .back:hover { color: var(--teal); }

  .legal {
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--fg);
    padding: clamp(48px, 7vw, 90px) 0 clamp(60px, 8vw, 100px);
  }
  .legal .wrap { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 34px; }

  .legal h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3.1rem);
    letter-spacing: -.02em; color: var(--ink);
    margin: 14px 0 0;
  }
  .legal .updated { color: var(--fg-3); font-size: 14.5px; margin: 10px 0 28px; }
  .legal h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--ink); margin: 38px 0 12px;
  }
  .legal p { font-size: 1.04rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--fg-2); margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .legal strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal ul { margin: 0 0 14px; padding-left: 22px; }
  .legal li { font-size: 1.04rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--fg-2); margin-bottom: 7px; }
  .legal a { color: var(--teal); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .legal a:hover { color: var(--teal-dark); }
  .legal .back-cta { margin-top: 44px; }
  .legal .back-cta a.btn-primary { text-decoration: none; color: #fff; }
  .legal .back-cta a.btn-primary:hover { color: #fff; }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .legal-top .wrap, .legal .wrap { padding-left: 22px; padding-right: 22px; }
  }
</style>
